Revising "extended" up from 95. I'm very sorry to see the death of democracy in the UK, but apparently remaining in the EU is more important than respecting a democratic vote. Sorry kids, our generation broke British democracy. It was fun while it lasted. Here's to the last 800 years. EDIT 26 Mar 2019;
May said at the dispatch box yesterday that the extension became legal in international law last Friday 22 May 2019 but in order for it to be binding in UK law, an act must pass through parliament. That will happen shortly. "The European Council agrees to an extension until 22 May 2019, provided the Withdrawal Agreement is approved by the House of Commons next week. If the Withdrawal Agreement is not approved by the House of Commons next week, the European Council agrees to an extension until 12 April 2019 and expects the United Kingdom to indicate a way forward before this date for consideration by the European Council." https://www.consilium.europa.eu/media/38744/21-euco-art50-conclusions-en.pdf Strasbourg document to get May's deal past Bercow;
